<br>
I have been playing the the kitty beastlord class for the last several days and have been having a lot of fun.  But as i look the spells and skills i will acquire as I grow higher in levels, I wonder about the viability of the beastlord class,especially in dungeon and planes fighting.<br>
<br>
While the pet appears to be the key to this class, how useful will the pet be in dungeons and planes. If they are like other pets, they can cause more harm than good, so if you ban the pets from these zones what do the beastlords add to a group?<br>
<br>
Melee abilities--strong offensive but weak defensive.  They can use blunt weapons only, but there are many good blunt weapons available, most monk blunt weapons appear to be bestlord usable.<br>
Beastlords have dual wield but can only wear leather armor. So while they should be very good damage dealers, they can only take very little damage before they die.  It would appear they depend on their pet to aggro the mobs.  <br>
With leather armor, I think you would you be better off with a shield rather than a second weapon?  It might have been better to give beastlord dual attack and not dual wield.<br>
They may be more similar to monks in regard to skills and armor, but according to what i have read their hand to hand skills top out at 100, so they are weapon dependent.<br>
<br>
<br>
Casting abilities--non pet related.<br>
It looks like magicians, wizards and druids are better at nuking, and druids and shammy's are better at both buffing and healing, clerics of course being the best healers.<br>
<br>
So why would you want a beastlord in your group?<br>
<br>
Obviously, the class has only existed for a few days, so we will all learn more as time goes on. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ugreywind15.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greywind15</A> at: 12/10/01 4:02:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uandvarishadowmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndvariShadowmist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bastard Bard</span><br>  Posts: 1522<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/10/01 6:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Viability of the Beastlord Class</span><hr size=1> Imho Beastlord seems like VI's answer to the casual player. It is a solo class that wont bring anything to a raid that others can't do better. <p><Center><a href = "mailto:andvari@thewarcouncil.com">Andvari Shadowmist</a><BR>
