ints of damage which also sucks up 75 points of mana.  It's a nice agro getter, but that's about it.  The dots remain newb shamy dots.  BL's are a nice back up to Shamy's and druids at mid level though.  I can out damage a bard (which isn't saying much), and my bufs are good enough for the non cleric healers to concentrate on keeping the main tank alive and throwing a nuke here and there, or possibly a debuffer.  Overall,  this class will probably not be real sought after at high level.  If your bored with your necro, and want do a little soloing from time to time this is a good class.  Otherwise stick to the base Warrior/cleric/rogue/chanter/shamy bunch. <p>Macalister WolfGuard -42nd Warrior /Morteux Thantos 52nd Heritic /Ardin Macalister 35th Bard/Clanncy Macalroy 32nd Beastlord(Saryrn) Questing to be the #1 Barbarian BL on the server.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukitsunesama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kitsune Sama</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(1/29/02 5:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Viability of the Beastlord Class</span><hr size=1> I get a feeling that the class is unfinshed. They only have two discs, resistant and fearless. Also the spells dont seem to be well thought out. I get the first evocation spell at level 30. Its a pain in the ass to raise. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gorra>Gorra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Ale Swiller</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/1/02 5